*--------------------------*
| Compute thickness values |
*--------------------------*

Inputs : 
-------

1) A mesh ( OFF file )
2) A resolution ( for voxelization )
3) An option describing where the thickness will be evaluated :
  -v : for each voxel of the binary object
  -d : by discretisation ( precise the step of the discretisation )
  -mc : by Monte-Carlo method ( random points, precise the number. )

Be careful ! With the last method, the number of points where the thickness will be evaluated
depend on the input number and on the volume of the object. This number will be print in consol
when the calculations stop.


thicknessFromSpheres: just load a set of spheres



Output : normalized thickness values
--------

To compile  :
-------------

mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
cmake .. 
make

To use :
--------

For each voxel :
./thickness path/to/the/object.off resolution -v 

By discretisation :
./thickness path/to/the/object.off resolution -d step

By Monte-Carlo :
./thickness path/to/the/object.off resolution -mc nbPts

examples :

./thickness ~/Documents/myObject1.off 250 -v
./thickness ~/Documents/myObject2.off 100 -d 200
./thickness ~/Documents/myObject1.off 300 -mc 4000000
